Mongodb -> is a Nosql database it does not have any  any schema and it provide high scalability and faster document retrival

mongoshell is used to connect the mongodb  instance running on local:27017

command=>

mongosh

output =>

Current Mongosh Log ID:	679707dd5812003a313f6bd6
Connecting to:		mongodb://127.0.0.1:27017/?directConnection=true&serverSelectionTimeoutMS=2000&appName=mongosh+2.3.8
Using MongoDB:		8.0.4
Using Mongosh:		2.3.8

For mongosh info see: https://www.mongodb.com/docs/mongodb-shell/

------
   The server generated these startup warnings when booting
   2025-01-27T09:06:44.414+05:30: Access control is not enabled for the database. Read and write access to data and configuration is unrestricted.

to show the available database

command =>

show dbs

result=>

admin    40.00 KiB
appdb   144.00 KiB
config   48.00 KiB
local    88.00 KiB

switch to the new database if exits else it will existing databse

command=>

use appdb

result=>

switched to db appdb


to show all the available collections in database

command=>

show collections

result=>

student
users

